    slug: "how-the-prophet-muhammad-peace-be-upon-him-performed-hajj",
    description: `How the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) Performed Hajj is an English-language Islamic book that provides a detailed, step-by-step account of the Hajj as it was performed by the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) during his Farewell Pilgrimage (Hajjat al-Wada') in the year 10 AH (632 CE). This pilgrimage, which took place only a few months before the Prophet's passing, serves as the definitive model for how the Hajj should be performed, and the Prophet explicitly instructed his companions, saying, "Take from me your rites of Hajj." This book meticulously follows that instruction by reconstructing every aspect of the Prophet's Hajj based on the detailed narrations found in the authentic hadith collections.

The book begins with the context of the Farewell Pilgrimage, explaining when and why the Prophet decided to perform Hajj, who accompanied him from Madinah, and the sermons and teachings he delivered during the journey. It then provides a comprehensive walkthrough of each stage of the Hajj as performed by the Prophet, beginning with the assumption of ihram at Dhul-Hulayfah, the entrance into Makkah, the tawaf al-qudum (arrival circumambulation) and sa'i between Safa and Marwa, and the delivery of the famous Farewell Sermon at Arafah — one of the most significant speeches in human history in which the Prophet summarized the core teachings of Islam.

Each subsequent ritual is described in meticulous detail, including the standing at Arafah, the journey to Muzdalifah, the stoning of the pillars at Mina, the sacrifice of the animal, the shaving or trimming of the hair, the tawaf al-ifadah (return circumambulation), and the remaining days at Mina. For each ritual, the book provides the exact actions of the Prophet (peace be upon him), the relevant Quranic verses and hadith narrations, and the scholarly consensus regarding the correct method of performing each act. The book distinguishes between the essential components of Hajj (arkan), the obligatory acts (wajibat), and the recommended acts (sunan), explaining the consequences of omitting each category. It also addresses common questions and practical issues that modern pilgrims may face. Written in clear and accessible English, this book serves as an authoritative reference for anyone planning to perform Hajj or Umrah, for Islamic teachers and imams who need to instruct others about the pilgrimage, and for students of Islamic jurisprudence who want to understand the evidential basis for the Hajj rituals.`,
